dcterms:description: The Comma.ai dataset provides a set of high-quality consistent driving data on the highway scenario, containing 7.5 hours of highway driving with sensor input recorded at 20 Hz, including images, car speed, acceleration, steering angle, GPS coordinates, and gyroscope angles.
dcterms:title: Comma.ai dataset

dcterms:description: The Udacity simulation environment is an open-source simulator developed based on Unity, providing a realistic 3D visualization of vehicle driving on three tracks in different environments, allowing for easy recording of human driver actions and access to control actions along with sensory perception information.
dcterms:title: Udacity simulation environment

dcterms:description: The Imagenet dataset contains 1.2 million images of approximately 1000 different classes, widely used for training deep learning models for image classification tasks.
dcterms:title: Imagenet dataset

dcterms:description: The FCN-LSTM architecture dataset is a larger crowd-sourced dataset used for end-to-end learning of driving models from large-scale video datasets, enabling the development of generic driving models.
dcterms:title: FCN-LSTM architecture dataset
